# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  ZAIM configuration
#
#  Two ways to run Zaim:
#
#  A) MULTI-USER (companies, Vercel, the desktop app) — RECOMMENDED
#     Users sign up and configure EVERYTHING from the web UI:
#       • their mailbox (IMAP/SMTP host, port, user, password, sender identity)
#         → stored AES-256-GCM encrypted, per user
#       • their agent/CLI keys → "🔑 Agent keys" in the app (generated + revoked
#         in the UI; each key reads/sends from that user's mailbox)
#     So a deployer sets ONLY the two server secrets below — nothing per-org.
#     The IMAP/SMTP/FROM/API_KEY blocks further down are NOT needed in this mode.
#
#  B) SINGLE-ACCOUNT (one deployment, one shared mailbox, no sign-up)
#     Fill the whole file. Good for a personal instance or a single-team box.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

#  ── Server secrets (mode A + B) — set ONCE per deployment, never per-org ──────
#  Postgres connection string. REQUIRED on Vercel / any serverless host (they have
#  no writable disk, so the default SQLite file can't work). Neon/Supabase/Vercel
#  Postgres all work — paste their URL here. Leave BLANK for local dev + the
#  desktop app, which fall back to a local SQLite file automatically.
POSTGRES_URL=

#  Master key that encrypts every stored mailbox password. REQUIRED for multi-user.
#  Generate: openssl rand -hex 32
ZAIM_ENC_KEY=
#  Signs login sessions. Generate: openssl rand -hex 32  (falls back to ZAIM_API_KEY)
ZAIM_SESSION_SECRET=
#  Turn on multi-user sign-up even without ZAIM_ENC_KEY set (not recommended):
# ZAIM_MULTIUSER=1

#  ═══ Everything below is ONLY for mode B (single shared account) ═════════════
#  In multi-user mode users set these per-mailbox in the UI — leave blank.

#  Legacy shared agent key (mode B). In multi-user mode, prefer per-user keys
#  generated in the app. Generate: openssl rand -hex 32
ZAIM_API_KEY=

#  IMAP (inbound)
ZAIM_IMAP_HOST=
ZAIM_IMAP_PORT=993
ZAIM_IMAP_SECURE=true
ZAIM_IMAP_USER=
ZAIM_IMAP_PASS=

#  SMTP (outbound) — falls back to IMAP user/pass if omitted
ZAIM_SMTP_HOST=
ZAIM_SMTP_PORT=465
ZAIM_SMTP_SECURE=true
ZAIM_SMTP_USER=
ZAIM_SMTP_PASS=

#  Sender identity
ZAIM_FROM_NAME=
ZAIM_FROM_EMAIL=
ZAIM_REPLY_TO=
